The Governor shall appoint a Board of Nursing consisting of sixteen (16) members:
Nine (9) members shall be registered nurses licensed to practice in the Commonwealth, with the Governor ensuring that the appointees represent different specialties from a broad cross-section of the nursing profession after soliciting and receiving nominations from recognized specialty state component societies;
Three (3) members shall be practical nurses licensed to practice in the Commonwealth;
One (1) member shall be a nurse service administrator who is a registered nurse licensed to practice in the Commonwealth;
One (1) member shall be engaged in practical nurse education who is a registered nurse licensed to practice in the Commonwealth; and
Two (2) members shall be citizens at large, who are not associated with or financially interested in the practice or business regulated.

Each appointment shall be for a term of four (4) years expiring on June 30 of the fourth year. The cycle for appointments and expiration of terms shall be as follows:
The first year of the four (4) year cycle, the terms for three (3) registered nurses and one (1) licensed practical nurse shall expire;
The second year of the four (4) year cycle, the terms for three (3) registered nurses and one (1) citizen at large shall expire;
The third year of the four (4) year cycle, the terms for two (2) registered nurses, one (1) licensed practical nurse, and the one (1) member engaged in practical nurse education who is a registered nurse shall expire; and
The fourth year of the four (4) year cycle, the terms for two (2) registered nurses, one (1) licensed practical nurse, and one (1) citizen at large shall expire.
